<paragraph id="1082F6EB5F81F3FE6DC7E791A6B297CF" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">Runde Zyperbinse</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="EC9270F08D901B9CC7ADD3EE408070EA" pageId="null" pageNumber="394" type="description">
<paragraph id="2889BA98ED2F040039078238E03368DB" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="B279D9DA6624277B0F9EC6C61501E9D1" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Cyperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="394" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longus">
<emphasis id="8B2A59BDA1C31967C1A8F704ED3D6583" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">C. longus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 7) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="C7750B78F8C62097618247D27F95D52B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">
Pflanze 10-40 cm hoch, mit 
<normalizedToken id="9C9C0B5CE22F93E57A91F6D557CD056D" originalValue="dünnen" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">duennen</normalizedToken>
, kaum 
<normalizedToken id="C9C8C16E3A74388E621B52BC17D6F708" originalValue="über" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">ueber</normalizedToken>
1 mm dicken, unterirdischen 
<normalizedToken id="0C25EFC8A76B6650D62774C11F5D2553" originalValue="Ausläufern" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">Auslaeufern</normalizedToken>
;
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="CE2E433CB2B181813B9EC3E57528D3E2" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
meist weniger als 4 mm breit; 
<normalizedToken id="EE2D44B9F1836F85EC4828A47EDB9CDD" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
kleiner. - 
<normalizedToken id="4B07FC6FB6460661CC672E314D0159EC" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1C511CA55381C57CEF52C66627529B0" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">
<emphasis id="6980B5A6FB05C8BC26DEFBFFE77CC42F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="26A42E5D71329B7EA2AFA4D82A3B88C6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">108:</emphasis>
Material aus Japan; Chromosomen sehr klein (Tanaka 1937). Pollen- und Embryosackentwicklung von Khanna (1965) untersucht; keine Angaben 
<normalizedToken id="21A26F91F1A80D0B1793EC312748B05D" originalValue="über" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">ueber</normalizedToken>
Chromosomen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4892C1DD57C72C88CF95A73C9693D70F" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">
<emphasis id="C65B20BE92C69E8CA68C3C70A1E0A076" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">Standort.</emphasis>
Wie 
<taxonomicName id="45529F683A5A52D4E021CC71FB82924D" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Cyperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="394" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longus">
<emphasis id="E680D75A8BD5F39BC8C6118085266125" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">C. longus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 7).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="11F21DDDE347F58DE2AB22BD17CBD33E" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">
<emphasis id="A7BCFFCDF9455B8BB6EDEEC147440DEC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="394">Verbreitung. Pflanze mit weltweiter Verbreitung:</emphasis>
Tropische und subtropische Gebiete der ganzen Erde. - Im Gebiet: Langensee, Luganersee, Comersee; selten.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
